Key Match Events: Džeko scored from a corner in the 70th minute.
Deniz Undav scored two goals, one in the 29th minute and another in the 35th minute.
Three goals were ruled out due to offside.
Pre-Game Insights: Julian Nagelsmann is dealing with many injuries but expectations are high for Germany.
Alexander Nübel is set to start as the goalkeeper for Germany against Bosnia and Herzegovina, with Oliver Baumann expected to play against the Netherlands.
With ter Stegen expected to be out for almost a year, Nübel and Baumann have a chance to make a case for the German #1 keeper spot.
Post-Match Reflections: Germany made the second half needlessly complicated by allowing Džeko to score from a corner, but otherwise it was a comfortable performance.
Deniz Undav is looking like the striker that Germany have been begging for.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at Bilino Polje Stadium, Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina.
The kickoff was at 8:45 pm local time, 2:45 am EST.
